.C. (1897)|Maidstone United]], joined from the [[1970\u201371 Isthmian League|Isthmian League]]\n\nAt the end of the season [[Ramsgate Athletic F.C.|Ramsgate Athletic]] was renamed Ramsgate.\n\n===League table===\n{{Infobox football league season\n|competition= Southern Football League<br>Division One South\n|season=1971\u201372\n|winners= [[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n|promoted= [[Ramsgate Athletic F.C.|Ramsgate Athletic]]<br>[[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n|matches= 240\n|total goals= 661\n|prevseason= [[1970\u201371 Southern Football League#Division One|1970\u201371]]\n|nextseason= [[1972\u201373 Southern Football League#Division One South|1972\u201373]]\n}}\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=PR\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n|winpoints=2\n|section=Division One South\n\n|team1=WAT|name_WAT=[[Waterlooville F.C.|Waterlooville]]\n|team2=RAM|name_RAM=[[Ramsgate F.C.|Ramsgate Athletic]]\n|team3=MAI|name_MAI=[[Maidstone United F.C. (1897)|Maidstone United]]\n|team4=RAW|name_RAW=[[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]]\n|team5=MET|name_MET=[[Metropolitan Police F.C.|Metropolitan Police]]\n|team6=TON|name_TON=[[Tonbridge Angels F.C.|Tonbridge]]\n|team7=BEX|name_BEX=[[Bexley United F.C.|Bexley United]]\n|team8=BAS|name_BAS=[[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n|team9=AND|name_AND=[[Andover F.C.|Andover]]\n|team10=ASH|name_ASH=[[Ashford Town F.C. (Kent)|Ashford Town (Kent)]]\n|team11=SAL|name_SAL=[[Salisbury City F.C.|Salisbury]]\n|team12=WCC|name_WCC=[[Winchester City F.C.|Winchester City]]\n|team13=HAS|name_HAS=[[Hastings United F.C.|Hastings United]]\n|team14=TRO|name_TRO=[[Trowbridge Town F.C.|Trowbridge Town]]\n|team15=CAN|name_CAN=[[Canterbury City F.C.|Canterbury City]]\n|team16=WOO|name_WOO=[[Woodford Town F.C. (1937)|Woodford Town]]\n|win_WAT=15|draw_WAT=9|loss_WAT=6|gf_WAT=40|ga_WAT=22\n|win_RAM=14|draw_RAM=11|loss_RAM=5|gf_RAM=42|ga_RAM=27\n|win_MAI=14|draw_MAI=10|loss_MAI=6|gf_MAI=48|ga_MAI=28\n|win_RAW=15|draw_RAW=5|loss_RA